Don't speak Portuguese? Click here to read a machine-translated version of the Portuguese article. Paraispolis ("Paradise city", possibly ironic, from paraiso paradise (Hisp.) and -opolis city (Greek))is a neighborhood of So Paulo city, which is part of the Vila Andrade district, in the south zone. It is derived from the Paraispolis favela, and has an estimated population between 80,000 and 100,000 people. It has about 20,000 households. Coordinates: 233700S 464336W / 23.6166667S 46.72667W / -23.6166667; -46.72667
